### Overview of the Hardware Community at SAINTCON

**Title:** COM - Hardware Community

**Date:** Conference Times 
- **Tuesday:** 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday:** 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Thursday:** 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Friday:** 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM
- **Monday:** Expo Closed

**Description:** 
The Hardware Hacking Community (HHC) is a platform for hardware enthusiasts to learn about soldering, repair, and hardware destruction. It offers a space for attendees to solder mini badges and take part in various projects.

**Services Provided:**
- Soldering equipment (irons, solder, etc.)
- Classes on how to solder with specific projects
- Tools for advanced diagnostics (oscilloscopes, multi-meters)

**What to Bring:**
- Personal electronic components/projects for soldering.

**Learning Opportunities:**
- Basic Hardware Structure
- Soldering Skills
- PCB Assembly Skills
- Electronic Components Identification

**MiniBadge:**
- A MiniBadge will be available at the community booth.

**Wallpaper:** 
Desktop wallpapers are available for download.

**Contact & Links:**
- **Website:** [SAINTCON](https://saintcon.org/com-hardware-community/)
- **Discord:** Join the SAINTCON community on Discord.
  
